name: Korean Soft Tofu Stew (Soon Du Bu Jigae)
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Korean chile powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ground beef (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Korean soy bean paste (doenjang)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) package', 'name': 'Korean soon tofu or soft tofu, drained and sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onion, chopped'}
steps: Heat the vegetable oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Stir in the Korean chile powder and ground beef. Cook and stir until the beef is crumbly, evenly browned, and no longer pink. Stir in the soy bean paste, coating the beef. Pour in the water and bring to a boil. Season with salt and pepper. Gently drop tofu into the soup and continue cooking until the tofu is heated through, 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat and quickly add the egg into the soup, stirring gently to break it up. Garnish with sesame seeds and green onion.

name: Easy Hoppin' John
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'smoked beef sausage, cut into bite-size pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '(15 ounce) cans', 'name': 'black-eyed peas, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10.75 ounce) cans', 'name': 'low sodium chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'uncooked instant rice'}
steps: Place sausage and onion into a large saucepan over medium heat; cook and stir until sausage begins to brown, about 10 minutes.. Stir in black-eyed peas, chicken stock, water, and cayenne pepper, and bring to a boil. Stir in rice; cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender, 20 to 25 minutes.

name: 'Momma Made Em' Chicken and Sausage Gumbo
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 pound)', 'name': 'whole chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen chopped onions'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen green bell peppers'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': "Cajun seasoning (such as Tony Chachere's), or to taste"}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'whole bay leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'fully-cooked smoked beef sausage (such as Hillshire Farm®), sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen sliced okra'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and black pepper to taste'}
steps: Fill a large pot partially with lightly salted water, and place the chicken in the pot. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat to a simmer, and cook the chicken until the meat is no longer pink and the juices run clear, about 1 hour. Remove the chicken from the broth, and crack open the carcass to allow the chicken to cool. Reserve the chicken broth. After the chicken has cooled enough to handle, pick the meat from the bones, and set aside.. While the chicken is simmering, make a roux by whisking together the flour and vegetable oil in a large, heavy saucepan over medium-low heat. Cook and stir the mixture, watching constantly to avoid burning, until the roux is a rich chocolate brown color, 20 to 30 minutes.. As soon as the roux has reached the desired color, stir in the onions, bell peppers, celery, Cajun seasoning, and bay leaves, and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes. Pour in the reserved chicken broth, diced tomatoes, and beef sausage, and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the mixture has thickened, about 1 hour.. Mix in the reserved chicken meat and okra, bring back to a simmer, and cook, stirring occasionally, until the okra is tender and the flavors have blended, 30 to 40 minutes.

name: Instant Pot Beef Stew with Red Wine
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'beef stew meat, cubed'}, {'quantity': '2 ¾', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry red wine'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped red potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'white onion, quartered'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped carrots'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped celery'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'sprigs', 'name': 'fresh rosemary'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bay leaf'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'egg noodles'}
steps: Combine flour, Italian seasoning, onion powder, salt, and pepper in a gallon-sized resealable plastic bag. Shake to mix seasoning. Add beef to bag, seal, and shake to coat.. Select Sear function on a multi-functional electric pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot) according to manufacturer's instructions. Add coated beef cubes and sear until lightly browned on all sides, 7 to 10 minutes. Pour in broth and red wine. Add tomato paste and garlic. Stir in potatoes, onion, carrots, celery, rosemary, and bay leaf.. Close and lock the lid. Select Stew setting and set timer for 25 minutes. Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build.. Release pressure using the natural-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, 10 to 40 minutes.. Meanwhile, fill a large pot with lightly salted water and bring to a rapid boil. Cook egg noodles at a boil until tender yet firm to the bite, 7 to 9 minutes. Serve alongside beef stew.

name: Beer Braised Irish Stew and Colcannon
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 pound)', 'name': 'beef chuck roast, trimmed of fat and cut into 1/2-inch cubes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) can or bottle', 'name': 'dark beer'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coarsely chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coarsely chopped carrot'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bay leaves'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'russet potatoes, peeled and cut into chunks'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'thinly sliced cabbage'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk, warmed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'minced fresh parsley'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C).. Make stew: Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat until very hot. Working in 2 batches, cook and stir beef in hot oil until browned. Return all of the meat to the Dutch oven, sprinkle with flour, and stir lightly to coat. Stir in beer, onion, carrot, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, thyme, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil and cover.. Place the Dutch oven into the preheated oven and cook for 45 minutes. Uncover, stir, and cook until beef is very tender and liquid is reduced by half, about 45 more minutes.. Meanwhile, make colcannon: Cook bacon in a large, deep skillet over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Drain bacon on a paper towel-lined plate. Crumble bacon and set aside.. About 30 minutes before stew is ready, place potatoes into a large pot and cover with salted water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain and allow to steam dry, 1 to 2 minutes.. Place cabbage into a microwave-safe bowl and add 1 to 2 tablespoons water. Cover and microwave on high for about 2 minutes 30 seconds; uncover (watch out for steam) and stir cabbage. Cover again and microwave until cabbage is slightly tender but not mushy, about 2 minutes 30 seconds more. Drain excess liquid and set cabbage aside, covered.. Place potatoes into a large bowl; add warm milk, butter, salt, and pepper. Beat with an electric mixer until smooth and creamy. Stir in cabbage, crumbled bacon, and parsley until well combined.. To serve, place a scoop of colcannon onto a plate, make a hollow, and fill with beef stew.

name: Beef Tinaktak
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lean ground beef'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'halved cherry tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': '(1-inch) sliced green onions'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light soy sauce, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemon, juiced, divided'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cube', 'name': 'beef bouillon (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced water chestnuts, halved'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': '1-inch cut green beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(13.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'coconut milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': "hot red chile pepper (donne'sali), chopped (Optional)"}
steps: Place beef in a large skillet over medium heat; cook and stir until browned, about 8 minutes. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels to drain excess grease.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion, tomatoes, green onions, 3 tablespoons soy sauce, 1/2 the lemon juice, garlic, beef bouillon, and black pepper. Cook and stir until flavors combine, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in water chestnuts and green beans; cook and stir until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.. Stir drained ground beef, remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce, and lemon juice into the skillet. Pour in coconut milk slowly; add chile pepper. Reduce heat to low and simmer until coconut milk is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat.

name: Caldereta (Filipino Beef Stew)
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'cubed beef stew meat'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, crushed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened pineapple juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red potatoes, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'carrot, sliced diagonally'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'miniature cocktail sausages'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'pineapple chunks, undrained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) can', 'name': 'medium pitted ripe olives, drained'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'bay leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce (such as Tabasco®) (Optional)'}
steps: Heat vegetable oil in a large pot over medium heat. Sprinkle beef with salt and black pepper and brown in the hot oil with garlic, about 10 minutes. Pour in water, pineapple juice, onion, tomato sauce, and tomato paste. Bring to a boil, turn heat to low, and simmer until beef is almost tender, 35 to 45 minutes.. name: Instant Pot Jamaican Oxtail Stew
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground allspice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'hickory-flavored liquid smoke'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'beef oxtails'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'beef broth, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'carrots, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'yellow onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'green onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Scotch bonnet chile pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) can', 'name': 'pinto beans, rinsed and drained'}
steps: Combine brown sugar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt, garlic powder, black pepper, allspice, cinnamon, and liquid smoke in a bowl. Add oxtails and toss until well coated.. Turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot) and select the Sauté function. When hot, add oil and place oxtails, flat-side down, inside. Brown on all sides, about 5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.. Pour 2 tablespoons beef broth into the pot to deglaze, scraping up all the browned bits from the bottom with a wooden spoon. Add carrots, onion, green onions, garlic, and Scotch bonnet pepper. Sauté until onions have softened, about 5 minutes. Return oxtails to the pot with remaining beef broth, ketchup, and thyme. Cancel the Sauté function.. Close and lock the lid. Select high pressure according to the manufacturer's instructions; set the timer for 45 minutes. Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build.. Release the pressure using the natural-release method according to the manufacturer's instructions, 20 to 40 minutes. Unlock and remove the lid.. Remove oxtails and vegetables from the pot, leaving the liquid behind. Select Sauté function and bring liquid to a simmer. Combine water and cornstarch in a small bowl; stir into the simmering liquid. Add pinto beans and simmer until liquid is slightly thickened and beans are warmed, about 5 minutes. Return oxtails and vegetables back to the pot, and mix to combine.

name: Hamburger Stew with Cabbage
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lean ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(15 ounce) cans', 'name': 'dark red kidney beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'cabbage, shredded'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cubes', 'name': 'beef bouillon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}
steps: Crumble ground beef into a large soup pot; cook and stir over medium-high heat until browned and crumbly, about 5 minutes. Drain grease. Add bell pepper, onion, and celery. Cook and stir for 5 minutes.. Increase heat to high. Add kidney beans, tomatoes, cabbage, beef broth, water, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon, and garlic; stir to combine. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer for 30 minutes.. Ladle soup into bowls and season with salt.

name: Cabbage Jambalaya
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'smoked sausage, cut into 1/4-inch slices'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium head', 'name': 'cabbage, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'stewed tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '14 ½', 'unit': 'fluid ounces', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked rice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'garlic salt, or to taste'}
steps: Combine ground beef, smoked sausage, onion, celery, and garlic in a large stock pot over medium-high heat. Cook and stir until beef is evenly browned, about 5 minutes. Stir in cabbage, tomatoes, water, and rice. Season with garlic salt.. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. Cover and cook, stirring once, until rice is tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
